article.headline: Centenary 95, IUPUI 83
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Odell Bradley scored 29 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead IUPUI to a 69-61 victory over Centenary on Saturday night. Matt Crenshaw added 21 points and was 11-of-12 from the free throw line for the Jaguars (17-9, 9-5 Mid-Continent), who had 32 points in the paint, while the Gents managed only 18. Centenary (15-10, 9-5) led once early in the first the half, and had only one player in double-digits, Andrew Wisniewski's game-high 34 points. IUPUI led 28-20 at the half and both teams scored 41 points in the second half as the Gents came up short. Matt Crenshaw added 21 points for the Jaguars, who outrebounded Centenary 35-21. The Gents shot 50 percent (9-of-18) from the 3-point line, while IUPUI connected on only 15.4 percent (2-of-15) of its 3-pointers.
